texts.text: >The fight between the Moirae sisters and
>the team of the youth turned hero and the Liberators goes on....
Yaaaa!
Hmmm, very nice...
But it is useless against us...
You're not going to stop him! I have his back!
As do I my sisters'!
Oof!!
Tsk, they're fast...!
>The Liberators are helping the young man,
>But no matter what they do, their attempts always fall short.
Their teamwork is so damn good! I guess it's because they're sisters.
Will you stop admiring them?! C'mon, we have to try again!

Yes, let's do this!
Yaaaa!!
You can try all you want.
But it is not in your fate to defeat us.
You should give up and use your power to fight the monsters instead.
There are still many who need your help here in this place.
If you help them, you will truly be a hero.
Then both we and the humans will get what we want.
You know that's what all badguys say when they know they can't win, right?
Do not interject, demon summoners. This is a conversation between a hero and the gods.
People who have sunken so low as to use the dark arts have no place here.
Here, let me cut the threads of your fate first.
>The sisters attack the Liberators...!
Shit! That's too much for us to handle...! Everybody dodge!!

You will NOT harm them!
Yaaaa!
...Hmmm.
>The young man's sword breaks the sisters' attacks.
Hey, that was a neat trick. You're not half bad.
Thanks for the help!
Pesky human...!
Hey, I got an idea. Are you in?
For what?
Like they said, we can't beat them with any of our attacks.
But what if we combined our attacks into one?
They always do that kinda stuff in superhero crossovers right? Combination moves!
...So the famous Megakin is into superheroes as well.
Who isn't into heroes that fight for truth and justice? We all look up to 'em.
Wait, you know who I am?!
As I said, you're famous.
To your viewers, you're kind of like a hero yourself.
Normally I'd be modest when I hear compliments like that,
but not today!
Aight, let's show those goddesses what a superhero crossover really looks like!
Yeah!
You guys down with that?!
Yes! Of course!
These so called goddesses like to lurk in the shadows and control people for their own entertainment.
Well, I'm ending their fun once and for all.
Hey, whatever it is you are conspiring, just give it up!
>Atropos rushes at them with shears in hand.
Now guys!
Come onnnnn!
You're going down!
Yaaaaa!
Take thisssss!
Heyaaaaa!
Ugh... My sisters...
>Atropos' body dissipates into light like unraveled yarn.
How's that, goddesses of fate? Now you two are next...!
*Chuckle*
*Laugh*
...What's so funny yo?
*Giggle*
What? She wasn't destroyed?!
Come now, there's no need to be alarmed, hero.
Yes, We no longer have to fight.
It hurt a little, but I forgive you. We got what we wanted after all.

You got what you wanted?
...Oh, this is what you were after...?!
They just wanted to see a hero in action and we gave them just that... Dammit!
Yoyoyoyoyo! Wait just a minute!
What about the people you brought here? What about all those who were killed?!
You did this to them just for your own entertainment...?! With no regard for their suffering and death?!
Huh? Oh, that...
Since this place is no longer needed, the threads that make up its fabric will be undone.
We have no use for them anymore.
W-What are you talking abou...?
Then this place should be...
returned to its original state.
There now everyone, come back to life to live it out as you are destined to.
>The sisters unravel the bundle of thread in their hands, and it starts to glow.
>And as woven by someone, it begins to take on human form.

What the...
What's happening...?
What do you mean by come back to life?!
Now, we must head back.
Yo wait! Why did you...
I spin the thread!
I measure the thread!
I cut the thread!

*Giggle*
But some other time maybe.
>The sisters fade as the people are resurrected.
>When the sisters have completely disappeared, everyone is back to normal.
Huh? I-I'm...?
How? I mean... How?
Why am I still alive? I died...
Oh. I-Is it really you, mister?
...Yeah. Yeah it's me! And you're that young man! I recognize the voice!
You recognize me?
Yeah of course. You're looking pretty heroic.
But... If it weren't for you...
>The young man bursts into tears.
>Out of the tracks of his tears, threads of light glisten then fade. The young man's appearance returns to normal...
Just got a call from Seiran... She said this place is falling apart.
I have no idea what's going on, but I think we should get the hell outa here!
Aight everybody, haul ass!
Everybody okay?
Looks that way. Is it... Over?
It better be.
Well, I think it's over.
I mean, with the people playing the villains gone, this heroic tale must end right?
>Megakin's eyes fall on the young man who is surrounded by people giving him praise.
So you beat the final boss? That's so cool!
Yes! Just like a real life superhero!
Not "just like", he's the real deal!
C'mon, stop saying that. To me, you're the real hero...
Me? I still owe you one remember?
>After a while the people went their separate ways,
>and the young man comes up to talk to the Liberators.
I just wanted to thank you guys again for what you've done.
Without your help, I never would've been able to save those people...
Well, it was a team effort.
Yo, what you said when you went full superhero mode though, that was pretty awesome stuff.
Ugh, don't remind me. Anyways, I'm back to just plain old me now.
...But I guess something did change in me.
What's that?
I still want help from other people, but now I'd like to be able to help others too.
As long as it's something I'm capable of doing of course.
...What I'm saying is that I'd like to be somebody's hero if I can.

I feel ya dude.
Sounds good to me.
We all have our limits, but we gotta spread the love man. A little bit of kindness, one person at a time.
Ain't that right, Shionyan?
The world's already a brighter place just by having me be in it, so I've done my part.

*Chuckle*
You guys crack me up.
Well, I'd better get going. Thank you again!
Yeah. See ya around, hero.
The hero we desired was found, even in this age.
That knowledge alone was all we needed.
Then maybe next time, we should give our hero a fitting adversary...?
*Chuckle*
*Laugh*
*Giggle*
